# Ilka, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Ilka (; , Elkhi) is a rural locality (a selo) in Zaigrayevsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 2,168 as of 2010. There are 17 streets.
Geography
Ilka is located 25&nbsp;km southeast of Zaigrayevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Shene-Busa is the nearest rural locality.
